info.name: sanityConfigBulkUpdate
info.description: this script tests all BulkUpdate endpoints based on a json created from regressionDiagram.json

exec: // To fix CMCF-1446: intermittent failure with 504 returns in Jenkins for bulk update sanity script

request.description: Deletes a node by record id

"description" for all nodes are changed from null to string

"controlOrder" for all controls relations are changed from 0 to 1

request.description:
The payload contains nodes of Floor4, Zone7, Zone8, Zone9, Keypad7, WALC2, WALC3, and PlugLoad1, in bottom-up order;

and the payload contain some of the relations between these 8 nodes, including both contains and controls.

All properties of the nodes and relations are removed except their ids.

If this bulk update Delete succeed, then 8 nodes and 14 relations will be moved (including the contains relation goes into Floor 4).

exec: pm.expect(jsonData.values[i].description).to.equal("was null now updated to a string");

request.description:
The payload contains nodes of Floor3, Zone6, Keypad6, WALCLum1, and OCS5, in bottom-up order;

and the payload does NOT contain any of the relations between these 5 nodes.

All properties of the nodes and relations are removed except their ids.

If this bulk update Delete succeed, then 5 nodes and 8 relations will be moved (including the contains relation goes into Floor 3).

exec: pm.expect(jsonData.values[i].description).to.equal("was null now updated to a string");

request.description:
hashId is generated from inNodeId, outNodeId, relationType, and other attributes. 

However, polaris team can not use the hashId to bulk delete a relation, and polaris team has a hard time to tell the id of a relation, so we decided to support use a combination of the following to bulk delete relations.

inNodeId, outNodeId, relationType, and other attributes.
